## Changes

### Added

#### Workspace Configuration (`.vscode/`)
- **`.vscode/rulebook.md`** — MANDATORY standards document (958 lines)
  - 11 comprehensive sections covering architecture, naming conventions, logging, error handling
  - Automatically discovered by Copilot for standards enforcement
  - Referenced in `.vscode/settings.json` as [CRITICAL] STANDARD_REFERENCE
  
- **`.vscode/settings.json`** — Workspace-level configuration
  - [CRITICAL] markers for mandatory review before any changes
  - References to rulebook.md for developer standards
  - Copilot integration configuration
  
- **`.vscode/extensions.json`** — 20 recommended VS Code extensions
  - Ensures consistent development environment across team
  
- **`.vscode/.copilotignore`** — Exclusion patterns for Copilot analysis
  - Prevents Copilot from analyzing non-essential files

#### AI Assistant Guidelines
- **`.aichat`** (root level, 228 lines) — MANDATORY for all AI assistants
  - 8-category critical checklist before making changes
  - Violation table and reference documents
  - Common patterns and best practices

#### Documentation Improvements
- **`docs/01-requirements/error-codes.json`** — Centralized error codes
  - Moved from multiple locations for single source of truth
  - 8 defined error codes (ERR_001 through ERR_008) with HTTP status mappings
  
- **`docs/05-validation-system/`** — New folder for validation documentation
  
- **`docs/06-changelogs/`** — Proper changelog directory structure
  - Master changelog: `docs/06-changelogs/changelog.01022026.001`
  - Per-PR changelogs: `docs/06-changelogs/ddmmyyyy.<sequence>`

#### Reorganized Infrastructure
- **`infrastructure/`** folder structure
  - `infrastructure/database/initialization/` — Database schema and init scripts
  - `infrastructure/database/maintenance/` — Query and maintenance scripts
  - `infrastructure/database/config/` — PostgreSQL configuration files
  - `infrastructure/data/seeding/` — SQL data seeding scripts
  - `infrastructure/tools/` — Utility and launch scripts

#### Consolidated Application Code
- **`app/`** folder structure
  - `app/client/` — Angular frontend (consolidated)
  - `app/server/` — .NET backend (consolidated)

